  <!-- Applications -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-surface" aria-labelledby="apps-heading">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="section-label text-accent mb-4">Applications</div>
      <h2 id="apps-heading" class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold text-ink tracking-wide mb-8">
        MDR Conveyor <span class="text-accent">Applications</span>
      </h2>
      <div class="text-lg text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-6">
        <p><strong class="text-ink">Distribution and fulfillment:</strong> MDR dominates new distribution center conveyor installations. Totes, shipping cartons, and polybag mailers route through pick modules, merge onto trunk lines, and <a href="/conveyor-types/accumulation-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">accumulate</a> before shipping sorters. Dematic, Intelligrated, TGW, and Bastian Solutions build large-scale fulfillment systems around MDR platforms. The quiet operation (55-65 dB) improves the working environment in facilities where hundreds of feet of conveyor run simultaneously.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">E-commerce order processing:</strong> E-commerce facilities process high volumes of small, lightweight items. MDR conveyors handle the variable product mix (poly bags, padded envelopes, small boxes) at 60-150 FPM with ZPA that prevents damage during accumulation. <a href="/resources/automated-conveyor-systems/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Automated conveyor systems</a> integrate MDR zones with barcode scanners, print-and-apply labelers, and <a href="/conveyor-types/diverting-merging/sortation/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">sortation systems</a>.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Packaging line accumulation:</strong> MDR provides the cleanest ZPA for <a href="/industries/packaging-line-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">packaging lines</a>. Cases, cartons, and shrink-wrapped packs queue between fillers, labelers, case packers, and palletizers without backpressure damage. The 24VDC architecture eliminates the pneumatic infrastructure that belt-driven accumulation systems require.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink"><a href="/industries/food-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Food and beverage:</a></strong> MDR rollers are available in stainless steel with IP54/IP65 rated motors for wet environments. <a href="/industries/food-conveyors/sanitary/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Sanitary MDR systems</a> feature open-frame construction and sealed motors. The absence of exposed belts and chains simplifies cleaning and reduces contamination risk.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Before <a href="/conveyor-types/transfer-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">transfers</a> and merges:</strong> MDR zones upstream of pop-up transfers, merges, and sortation diverters provide precise product positioning. The zone controller holds each product at a known position and releases it on command, ensuring reliable transfer timing. This eliminates the product spacing variability that causes transfer jams on continuous-run conveyors.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink"><a href="/conveyor-functions/indexing-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Indexing applications:</a></strong> MDR zones provide stop-and-go indexing for robotic pick-and-place, vision inspection, labeling, and printing stations. Each zone acts as a precision positioning station. The motor controller stops the product at the sensor position with repeatable accuracy.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
