      <h2 id="selection-heading" class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold text-ink tracking-wide mb-8">
        When to Choose <span class="text-accent">MDR</span>
      </h2>
      <div class="text-lg text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-6">
        <p><strong class="text-ink">Choose MDR when:</strong></p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-2">
          <li>You need zero-pressure accumulation without pneumatic infrastructure</li>
          <li>Product weight is under 250 lbs per zone</li>
          <li>Energy efficiency is a priority (50%+ savings over continuous-run systems)</li>
          <li>Low noise is important (55-65 dB vs 70-85 dB for belt/chain systems)</li>
          <li>You want minimal maintenance (no belts, chains, or O-rings between motor and driven shaft)</li>
          <li>You need easy future expansion (add zones without new motors or pneumatics)</li>
          <li>24VDC Class 2 wiring simplifies your electrical installation</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Choose <a href="/conveyor-types/roller-conveyors/powered/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">belt-driven live roller</a> instead when:</strong> product weight exceeds 300 lbs, you need speeds above 200 FPM, or upfront cost is the primary constraint and you do not need accumulation.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Choose <a href="/conveyor-types/cdlr-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">CDLR</a> instead when:</strong> product weight exceeds 500 lbs (pallets, drums), you need positive chain drive with zero slip, or <a href="/industries/packaging-line-conveyors/pallet/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">pallet handling</a> is the primary application.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Choose <a href="/conveyor-types/roller-conveyors/gravity/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">gravity roller</a> instead when:</strong> no powered transport is needed, a slight decline is available, and budget is the top constraint.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

