          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">
            <p>MDR stands for Motor Driven Roller. A 24VDC brushless DC motor sits inside the roller tube, creating an independent drive zone. See our <a href="/conveyor-types/roller-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">roller conveyor hub</a> for all roller types.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What are the advantages over belt-driven roller?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">
            <p>Built-in ZPA without pneumatics, 50%+ energy savings, quieter (55-65 dB), less maintenance, easier expansion. Higher upfront cost but lower total cost of ownership. See the <a href="/conveyor-types/live-roller-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">live roller comparison</a>.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What weight can MDR handle?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">
            <p>Standard MDR: 50-250 lbs per zone. For heavier loads, use <a href="/conveyor-types/roller-conveyors/powered/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">belt-driven live roller</a> (up to 500 lbs) or <a href="/conveyor-types/cdlr-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">CDLR</a> (up to 10,000 lbs).</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            How does MDR zone control work?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">
            <p>Each zone has one motorized roller, 2-4 slave rollers, a photo-eye sensor, and a zone controller card. The controller reads the sensor and communicates with adjacent zones. When downstream is occupied, the upstream zone holds its product with a gap , creating <a href="/conveyor-types/accumulation-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">zero-pressure accumulation</a>.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            Who manufactures MDR rollers?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">
            <p>Interroll (RollerDrive EC5000), Itoh Denki (PM series), and Rulmeca (RDR series) manufacture the rollers. Hytrol, Dematic, Intelligrated, TGW, and Bastian Solutions integrate them into complete systems.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
